   "\u003cp\u003e\n    We at the Teacher at Sea Program wish Elizabeth Bullock the best of luck as she begins a new journey in life! She is leaving the TAS Team as the Program\n    Support Specialist, to begin teaching a fifth and sixth grade class. Elizabeth will be missed very much and her new students are lucky to have her.\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\nElizabeth went to sea on the R/V \u003cem\u003eWalton Smith \u003c/em\u003ein December 2011. You can read her blogs here:    \u003ca href=\"http://teacheratsea.noaa.gov/2011/bullock.html\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ehttp://teacheratsea.noaa.gov/2011/bullock.html\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e",
