   "Careers on a NOAA Ship",
   "\u003cp\u003e\nAndrea Schmuttermair (TAS 2012) was aboard NOAA Ship \u003cem\u003eOregon II\u003c/em\u003e during a SEAMAP Summer Ground Fish Survey. While on her research cruise, Ms.\nSchmuttermair learned about NOAA Careers during an interview with one of the junior NOAA Corps officers. You can view the interview by going to Ms.\nSchmuttermair’s \u003ca href=\"http://teacheratsea.wordpress.com/2012/07/07/andrea-schmuttermair-back-on-solid-ground-july-7-2012/\"\u003eblog\u003c/a\u003e, and you can see the\nlesson plan that she wrote about NOAA Careers by going to the \u003ca href=\"http://teacheratsea.noaa.gov/2012/schmuttermair.html#lessons\"\u003e lesson tab of her page\u003c/a\u003e.\n\u003c/p\u003e",
