   "Susie Hill, (TAS,2007) Visits NOAA",
   "Headquarters in Norfolk, VA with her Explore the Bay Campers",
   "\u003cp\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"http://teacheratsea.noaa.gov/2007/hill/index.html\"\u003eSusie Hill\u003c/a\u003e\n, \u003ca href=\"http://www.nauticus.org/\"\u003eNauticus\u003c/a\u003e Education Specialist and NOAA Teacher at Sea '07, and her \u003cem\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://www.nauticus.org/programs-activities/summer-camp\"\u003eExplore the Bay\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/em\u003e Summer Campers had the field trip of a lifetime at the NOAA\nHeadquarters in Norfolk, VA on August 6, 2013. The six campers, ages 10-13, spent the day with NOAA Corps Officers LCDR Denise Gruccio and ENS Charles\nWisotzkey touring the \u003ca href=\"http://www.moc.noaa.gov/tj/\"\u003eNOAA Ship \u003cem\u003eThomas Jefferson\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cem\u003e \u003c/em\u003ewhere they saw spaces such as the Charting\nRoom, Galley, Damage Control Locker Equipment Room, and Navigation Bridge. They also had the opportunity to learn about ocean bathymetry with NOAA Physical\nScientist, Ms. Tyanne Faulkes while she demonstrated the processes of sidescan and multibeam sonar mapping.\n\u003c/p\u003e",
