   "Amanda Peretich (TAS, 2012) Visits NOAA Scientists",
   "at the Alaska Fisheries Science Center",
   "\u003cp\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"http://teacheratsea.noaa.gov/2012/peretich.html\"\u003eAmanda Peretich\u003c/a\u003e, (TAS, 2012) was one of twenty teachers selected as a participant in the 2013 \u003ca href=\"http://siemensstemacademy.com/index.cfm?event=showPage&amp;p=programOverview\"\u003eSiemens Science Teachers As Researchers (STARs)\u003c/a\u003e Program at the\nPacific Northwest National Laboratories (PNNL) in July. After two weeks of research immersion at PNNL, Ms. Peretich went to \u003ca href=\"http://www.afsc.noaa.gov/\"\u003eNOAA Fisheries Alaska Fisheries Science Center (AFSC)\u003c/a\u003e in Seattle, WA. She visited Neal Williamson and Denise\nMcKelvey, two NOAA research fish biologists who were on NOAA ship \u003cem\u003eOscar Dyson \u003c/em\u003eduring her TAS cruise in July 2012. The scientists set up lab tours\nand took her on a tour of the rest of the AFSC.\n\u003c/p\u003e",
   "\u003cp\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"http://teacheratsea.noaa.gov/2012/peretich.html\"\u003eAmanda Peretich\u003c/a\u003e, (TAS, 2012) was one of twenty teachers selected as a participant in the 2013    \u003ca href=\"http://siemensstemacademy.com/index.cfm?event=showPage&amp;p=programOverview\"\u003eSiemens Science Teachers As Researchers (STARs)\u003c/a\u003e Program at the\nPacific Northwest National Laboratories (PNNL) in July. After two weeks of research immersion at PNNL, Ms. Peretich went to    \u003ca href=\"http://www.afsc.noaa.gov/\"\u003eNOAA Fisheries Alaska Fisheries Science Center (AFSC)\u003c/a\u003e in Seattle, WA. She visited Neal Williamson and Denise\n    McKelvey, two NOAA research fish biologists who were on NOAA ship \u003cem\u003eOscar Dyson \u003c/em\u003eduring her TAS cruise in July 2012. The scientists set up lab tours\n    and took her on a tour of the rest of the AFSC.\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\n    Ms. Peretich will use the data from the Summer 2012 Alaskan Pollock Survey as a primary source in the classroom to have students analyze/interpret the\n    data, draw conclusions, and initiate future questions.\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e",
   "https://teacheratsea.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/amanda1-2.jpg?w=180",
   "(L-R) Denise McKelvey, Neal Williamson and Amanda Peretich at NOAA Fisheries AFSC",
   "08/22/2013",
   "MA"
