   "The \"Right\" Kind",
   "of Lessons",
   "\u003cp\u003e\nThe \"Right\" Kind of Lessons: \u003ca href=\"http://teacheratsea.noaa.gov/2013/greene.html\"\u003eAngela Greene\u003c/a\u003e (TAS, 2013) joined NOAA scientists on NOAA ship \u003cem\u003eGordon Gunter\u003c/em\u003e in May to survey the population of the critically endangered North Atlantic right whale. This gentle giant is listed under the \u003ca href=\"http://www.nmfs.noaa.gov/stories/2013/11/11_21_13esa_turns_40.html\"\u003eEndangered Species Act, which celebrates 40 years\u003c/a\u003e this December. In an\ninterview with NOAA Fisheries, Angela explains what she learned and what she’s sharing with her students.\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\nYou can read the NOAA Fisheries feature story \u003ca href=\"http://www.fisheries.noaa.gov/stories/2013/12/12_13_2013tas_right_whale_survey.html\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ehere\u003c/a\u003e.\n\n\u003c/p\u003e",
   "#",
