   "Rebecca Himschoot (TAS, 2007)",
   "Receives Presidential Award",
   "\u003cp\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"http://teacheratsea.noaa.gov/2007/himschoot/index.html\"\u003eRebecca Himschoot\u003c/a\u003e\n(TAS 2007) was one of 102 teachers nationwide to receive the 2012 \u003ca href=\"https://www.paemst.org/\"\u003ePresidential Award for Excellence in Mathematics and Science\u003c/a\u003e. The White House announced the winners of the nation’s\nhighest honor for teachers of math and science on December 20, 2013. Congratulations Rebecca!\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\nThe award includes a $10,000 cash prize from the National Science Foundation, a trip to Washington DC to meet President Obama, and a tour of the\nSmithsonian.\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\nYou can read more about Rebecca’s honor \u003ca href=\"http://www.alaskapublic.org/2014/01/06/sitka-teacher-wins-white-house-award/\"\u003ehere\u003c/a\u003e and view Rebecca’s\nprofile on the Presidential Awards for Excellence in Mathematics and Science Teaching Recognition Program \u003ca href=\"https://recognition.paemst.org/finalist_profile/29473\"\u003ehere.\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e",
