   "Rita Salisbury (TAS,2013)",
   "Volunteers at NOAA Heritage Week Open House",
   "\u003cp\u003e\nRita Salisbury (TAS, 2013) volunteered to share information about the NOAA Teacher at Sea Program and demonstrated fisheries hands-on activities at \u003ca href=\"http://preserveamerica.noaa.gov/hw14.html\"\u003eNOAA’s Heritage Week Open House\u003c/a\u003e on Saturday, February 15, 2014 at NOAA’s Science Center in Silver\nSpring, MD. A series of free activities was open to the public, including guest presentations, interactive exhibits, and hands-on activities for ages 5 and\nup. Ms. Salisbury shared her \u003ca href=\"http://teacheratsea.noaa.gov/2013/salisbury.html\"\u003eTAS experience\u003c/a\u003e aboard NOAA ship \u003cem\u003eOscar Elton Sette\u003c/em\u003e with\nthe community and explained how light waves in water provide camouflage for some deep sea bottomfish. NOAA’s Heritage Week is an annual event and is part\nof the \u003ca href=\"http://www.preserveamerica.gov/\"\u003ePreserve America Initiative.\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\nSussex Technical High School Article about Ms. Salisbury at NOAA Heritage Week Open House -\n\u003ca href=\"http://www.sussexvt.k12.de.us/school/j-pages/announce-list/1213-st-biology-teacher-is-invited-host-at-noaa-heritage-week-open-house\"\u003e\nClick Here\n\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e",
