   "Mid-Atlantic Region Teacher at Sea Alumni",
   "Attend Workshop at NOAA Headquarters",
   "\u003cp\u003e\nSeventeen NOAA Teacher at Sea Alumni from the Mid-Atlantic Region (DC, DE, MD, and VA) met in Silver Spring, MD on March 14 – 17, 2014 for a three-day workshop with the following objectives: \n\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n    \n    \u003cli style=\"list-style-type:disc\"\u003e\n        Enhance science content knowledge\n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli style=\"list-style-type:disc\"\u003e\n        Share local NOAA data and resources\n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli style=\"list-style-type:disc\"\u003e\n    Explore ways in which workshop content can be incorporated in curriculum\n\u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli style=\"list-style-type:disc\"\u003e\n     Develop a plan to work together and promote NOAA science in Mid-Atlantic schools and communities.\n\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\n    The workshop, held on NOAA’s Main Campus, included tours of NOAA’s Science Center and Auditorium, NOAA’s Science on a Sphere, and the Gateway to NOAA. Topics included geodesy, ocean circulation, tide prediction, measuring sea level, jellyfish and sponges history and evolution, and other ocean topics.\n\u003c/p\u003e",
