   "International Science and Engineering Fair (ISEF)",
   "\u003cp\u003e\n1,700 finalists from around the world competed at  \u003ca href=\"https://student.societyforscience.org/intel-isef\"\u003eIntel International Science and Engineering Fair \u003c/a\u003ein May, 2014 in Los Angeles, CA. Finalists\nqualify for Intel ISEF by participating in local, regional, state, or national fairs associated with  \u003ca href=\"https://www.societyforscience.org/mission-and-history\"\u003eSociety for Science &amp; the Public\u003c/a\u003e.\n\u003c/p\u003e",
   "\u003cp\u003e\n1,700 finalists from around the world competed at  \u003ca href=\"https://student.societyforscience.org/intel-isef\"\u003eIntel International Science and Engineering Fair \u003c/a\u003ein May, 2014 in Los Angeles, CA. Finalists\nqualify for Intel ISEF by participating in local, regional, state, or national fairs associated with  \u003ca href=\"https://www.societyforscience.org/mission-and-history\"\u003eSociety for Science &amp; the Public\u003c/a\u003e.\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\nJacqueline Hams, (TAS, \u003ca href=\"http://teacheratsea.noaa.gov/2006/hams/index.html\"\u003e2006\u003c/a\u003e and  \u003ca href=\"http://teacheratsea.noaa.gov/2011/hams.html\" \u003e2011\u003c/a\u003e), was invited by the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration’s Office of Education\nto judge the NOAA Special Award for outstanding projects in ocean, coastal, Great Lakes, weather, and climate sciences. More than 70  \u003ca href=\"https://student.societyforscience.org/special-awards-organizations\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eSpecial Award organizations\u003c/a\u003e provide educational scholarships, cash awards,\n    summer internships, and equipment grants.\n\u003c/p\u003e\n    View the \u003ca href=\"https://www.societyforscience.org/press-release-intel-isef-2014-special-award-winners\" target=\"_blank\"\u003efull list \u003c/a\u003eof Special Awards winners.\n\u003c/p\u003e",
